{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. As such, we often need to deprecate certain APIs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in favor of newer ones. We recommend people update their code as quickly as possible to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs, and this article contains some tips for doing so."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Asserting on action payloads","anchor":"Asserting-on-action-payloads","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In version 1.4 of the library we provided a new assertion method on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore"},{"text":" for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"asserting on actions received without asserting on the payload in the action (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4#Receiving-test-store-actions"},{"text":" for more information). However, sometimes it is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"important to assert on the payload, especially when testing delegate actions from child features,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and so that is why 1.6 introduces","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore\/receive(_:_:timeout:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-9jd7x"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you have code like the following for asserting that an action features sends a delegate action","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a specific payload:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["await store.receive(.child(.delegate(.response(true))))"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can now update that code to the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["await store.receive(\\.child.delegate.response, true)"]}]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Update your code to make use of the new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore\/receive(_:_:timeout:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-9jd7x"},{"text":" method when you need to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"assert on the payload inside an action received.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/Compo